Cloneable
public final class Capability
extends Object
implements Cloneable

A Capability is a boolean object property that can be referenced by index or name. The value of the boolean indicates if the property is available or unavailable. A Capability can optionally indicate if it can be enabled or disabled by calling code - this only makes sense if the capability is available. For example, a Layer may have caching capability available, and usually, outside code is allowed to enable or disable caching for that Layer. By contrast, a SpatialServer's admin ACL may choose to disable attribute queries for a particular service Layer - outside code is not allowed to re-enable this capability.
